Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Engineer role with Imagen Technologies. I bring over three years of professional experience designing and developing production software applications in Python, Java, Spring Boot, FastAPI, React, TypeScript, PostgreSQL, Redis, and AWS, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Imagen's mission to ensure every patient receives the right diagnosis at the right time strongly resonates with the way I build software: with technical rigor, measurable outcomes, and attention to the people relying on the system. At Sperse, I designed and developed a Machine Learning enabled CRM platform using Python, LangGraph, LangChain, and FastAPI that routes requests across 40+ specialized sub-agents with secure access control for 10,000+ users. I also created tickets, stories, and epics for a React Flow and TypeScript visual workflow platform, then built durable Temporal execution paths that let users create, run, and manage agentic swarms against business and user needs. That combination of implementation, planning, and user-centered execution maps directly to Imagen's need for engineers who can build software applications that support business and clinical workflows with precision.

I would also bring the engineering discipline and collaborative habits this role emphasizes. I conducted peer code reviews and built an agentic review pipeline integrating OpenAI Codex with a Bitbucket MCP server, improving code quality, consistency, and best practices across 25-30 PRs/week while reducing reviewer load by several hours. I created a FastMCP server and wrote technical documentation for 160+ backend actions, helping AI agents automate CRM workflows securely across multiple customers with built-in monitoring. I also built LlamaIndex-powered RAG agents using OpenAI embeddings and Pgvector to answer product questions, generate ready-to-run REST API examples, and support software system design and maintenance decisions. These experiences align with Imagen's values of thinking critically, delivering fast, building trust, and following through.

Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest I designed and developed Java and Spring Boot storage software applications with PostgreSQL and Redis, handling uploads, downloads, and deletions across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs. I applied Analysis of Algorithms reasoning to optimize PostgreSQL window functions, materialized views, and indexes, then delivered Data Visualization workflows in React so business stakeholders could inspect latency and scalability gains. I also consulted with customers and other departments on project status, proposals, and software system design or maintenance while orchestrating long-running jobs with AWS Step Functions, reducing AWS Lambda timeouts across 100K+ weekly executions. That background would help me contribute meaningfully to Imagen's core engineering responsibilities while supporting its broader goal of making high-quality diagnostic care more accessible through AI-enabled technology.

I have always been passionate about purpose-driven engineering, critical thinking, fast delivery, and building trust through reliable follow-through, and I would be excited to apply those values to Imagen's mission of helping patients receive accurate, timely diagnoses. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

